=== EXAMPLE: scdoc_Guides_FFT-Overview_ex9 ===

DESCRIPTION: A very_dark pure_tone sound, with square_like oscillator character around 50 Hz, featuring very_slow attack and sustained envelope, with chaotic spectral movement, filtered with steep_rolloff character, and spectrally simple.

CATEGORIES:
  attack_time: very_slow
  brightness: very_dark
  crest_factor_db: sustained
  envelope_flatness: flat
  harmonic_to_noise_ratio: pure_tone
  spectral_complexity_mean: simple
  spectral_flux_normalized: chaotic
  spectral_slope: steep_rolloff
  temporal_centroid: balanced

SYNTHESIS CONCEPTS (key values):
[oscillator]
  fundamental_freq: 50.0000
  harmonic_decay_rate: -9.0471
  harmonic_regularity: 0.8522
  pitch_clarity: 0.0000
  inharmonicity: 0.0000
  type: square_like
[filter]
  spectral_slope: -2.5094
  resonance_freq: 0.0000

SUPERCOLLIDER CODE:
// Title: FFT Overview Example 9
// Author: SC Documentation
// URL: http://doc.sccode.org/Guides/FFT-Overview.html
// Tags: FFT-Overview, Guides, spectral
// ---
// --- Example 9 ---
(
x = { var inA, chainA, chainB;
    inA = LFClipNoise.ar(100);
    chainA = FFT(LocalBuf(2048, 1), inA);
    chainB = PV_PhaseShift(chainA, pi);
    // half-circle phase shift should result in an inverse signal
    // in practice, ultra-low frequencies sneak through
    // but you won't hear very much here
    IFFT(chainA) + IFFT(chainB);
}.play;
)
